        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "The words of the righteous, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " i.e. the judgment of the righteous judges, i.e. of them who before were such, and are inclined to be so, and probably would be so, were they not tempted with bribes; or of them who by their place should be righteous. So they are called righteous, to admonish them of their duty to be so, and to aggravate their sin when they are unrighteous, and consequently to aggravate the mischief of gifts, which make those unrighteous whose office obligeth them to be righteous. Or thus, ",
        "children": []
