  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 8.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And thou shalt take no gift",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The worst sin of a judge, and the commonest in the East, is to accept abribe from one of the parties to a suit, and give sentence accordingly. As such a practice defeats the whole end for which the administration of justice exists, it is, when detected, for the most part, punished capitally. Josephus tells us that it was so among the Jews (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "Contr. Apion",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". 2:27); but the Mosaic code, as it has come down to us, omits to fix the penalty. Whatever it was, it was practically set at nought. Eli's sons \"turned aside after lucre, and took bribes, and perverted judgment\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 8:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). In David's time, men's hands were \"full of bribes\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 26:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Solomon complains of wicked men\" taking gifts out of their bosoms to pervert the ways of judgment\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 17:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Isaiah is never weary of bearing witness against the princes of his day, who\" love gifts and follow after rewards\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 1:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ");who \"justify the wicked for reward, and take away the righteousness of the righteous from him\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 5:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Micah adds his testimony  - \"Hear this, I pray you, ye heads of the house of Jacob and princes of the house of Israel, that ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "abhor judgment and pervert all equity",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". They build up Zion with blood, and Jerusalem with iniquity. The heads thereof judge for reward\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 3:9-11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The gift blindeth the wise",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 16:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Exodus 23:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
